    rationale: "The coin's signature figure-eight: two huge concentric-ring eyes welded at the midline (outer circles overlap 0.6 units, forming a solid junction bar), the brow band arcing over and riding welded along both ring tops, and the wedge beak hanging from the junction clearly below the eye line. Positive bold rings with 2.8-unit pupils and the beak-below-eyes geometry make it read owl (not skull) even at 14px, and there are no tufts or head outline to drift toward cat or robot.",
